The Mac Evaluation installer creates a *directory* called {{output.log}} in the {{CONFLUENCE_HOME/logs}} directory but it does not create proper log files.

E.g. for 3.4.8 {{CONFLUENCE_HOME}} can be found here:

{code}
/Users/$USER/Library/Application\ Support/Atlassian\ Evaluation/work/confluence/3.4.8/confluence-home 
{code}

When moving a page from one space to another, if you have an word surrounded in escaped brackets, it will be treated like a link and the old space will be prefixed to your word.

Example:
{noformat}The atom:id is identified in the atom specification as an "element \[that\] conveys a permanent, universally unique identifier for an entry or feed."{noformat}

Will be translated to:
{noformat}The atom:id is identified in the atom specification as an "element \[oldspace:that\] conveys a permanent, universally unique identifier for an entry or feed."{noformat}

When the page is moved to a different space.

When I search for stuff that I wrote I enter my username into the Who field: {{jed}}

When it returns the Who field is populated with a nice expansion of my full name: {{Jed Wesley-Smith (jed)}}

If I then edit my search and leave this field as it is, the search returns nothing and the field has a validation error: {{No matching user found.}}

