When adding to UserLoggedInCondition to a WebPanel I kept getting context.getUser() returning null when a user was definitely logged in. The problem is that this WebPanel was being included via this call:

{code}
#webPanelForLocation("atl.header" $action.context)
{code}

in header.vm. The vm is parsed by #standardHeaderWithStylesheetAction which is called from #standardHeader which is called in the <head> of main.vmd. Thus, at the point where $action.context is being put in the webPanelForLocation call, the action is the dummy ConfluenceActionSupport object created in GeneralUtil.newWiredConfluenceActionSupport for rendering sitemesh.

The getContext method in CAS.java is missing most of the properties of WebInterfaceContext - e.g. 'user', but when the shouldDisplay method of UserLoggedInCondition is called, it's a WebInterfaceContext that is passed in.

This does not make sense.

