I'd like to be able to add a 'directed' comment to a Confluence page. The idea would be that when I add a comment, I can pick one or more users to direct that comment to. Those users would receive email notification that there is a comment directed to them. Replies should also be directed.

Normally a comment is added to a page and all watchers are notified, which is fine if everyone is watching every page. But there are many times where I want someone to take a look at a page and I have to add a comment and then email them to go look at the comment. This feature would eliminate that extra step and make collaboration easier.

A simple search box above the comment text box would be all that's needed.

