Importing a Word document with a number of embedded images can sometimes result in OutOfMemory errors (see: [CONF-21717|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-21717]).

Compressing the file in Word 2007+ resolves the problem, however not everyone has access to this. It would be helpful to either show a warning when importing Word documents, or perhaps compress them automatically during the add process.

To replicate:

# Create test source page consisting of ToC macro and headings/text
# Create test target page and include the source page using includes macro

Result: Table of Contents will appear in target page but links will not work.

{panel:title=Workaround|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}

Remove the ToC macro from the source page and instead use it in the target page:

{noformat}
{toc}

{include:<SOURCE_PAGE_TITLE>}
{noformat}
{panel}

When using a markup like [!teste.gif!|Confluence Documentation Home], in a page using Easy Reader Theme in order to insert a image with link on Confluence, it will not be clickable on IE7.

Workaround:

1- Go to <confluence-installation> >> confluence >> WEB-INF >> classes >> com >> atlassian >> confluence >> setup

2- Open the file fixedwidth.css from atlassian-bundled-plugins.zip >> fixedwidth-theme-3.3.3.jar >> fixedwidth >> css


3- Then comment the lines within the image-wrap class as follows:


{code}
.image-wrap {
    /*display:inline-block;
    overflow-y: hidden;
    overflow-x:auto;
    max-width:100%;*/
}

{code}

